loops which circulate demineralized water between the re-
actor vessel and steam generators. Each loop consists of two
motor pumps, two swing check valves, two electrically op-
erated gate valves, a steam boiler, and connecting piping.
The design conditions for all parts are 1800 psig and 650F.
The principle material of construction for components com-
ing in contact with the coolant is type 304 stainless steel.

The primary coolant pumps are single speed centri-
fugal pumps which are mounted on the head of the steam
generator and supported by the piping. Water is provided
for the cooling of the pumps during normal operation. The
pumps, however, are required to operate without cooling
