However, drag-lines are only designed to dig loose dirt
and rock. They do not dig well through hard packed soil or
solid rock formations. So the earth must be loosened by
drilling and blasting before the drag-line can dig. The drill-
ing is done by a large rotary drilling unit. The one described
here is a larger type and can drill through 50 ft. of solid
rock in about 20 minutes. The diesel engine on the drilling
rig is used to drive hydraulic pumps, and an air compressor.
The drill is turned by hydraulic motors and air is blown
through the drill stem to blow out the dust.

