demonstrated that such double-grip latches resisted separa-
tion of the lock components during a collision and the door
remained closed. These latches are, by no means foolproof;
Under excessive impact these latches would simply shear
apart but under the lessor load that is applied in the
majority of accidents they will hold up fine in most in-
stances.

The most effective single item of protective equipment
presently available to reduce traffic injuries and death is the
automotive seat belt. Thousands of lives are lost each year
because people are thrown against windshields or out of car

