The traditional homecoming festivities at the University
of Pittsburgh featured the fraternity-sorority float parade.
Each float had to conform with the general theme, Broad-
way Shows, and also had to have an association with the
Pitt-West Virginia football game.

Eachgroup was confronted with similar problems when
attempting to build a float, many of which can be a test of
an Engineer’s basic skill.

The first and possibly hardest problem was deciding on
a theme. A joint meeting was held. between the fraternity
and sorority to do this. The idea of building the float around
the show “Streetcar Named Desire” was mentioned and dis-
cussed, but later discarded. When “Showboat” was men-
tioned it seemed that everybody got the same idea at the
same time. It was unanimously decided to build a Mississippi
River stern wheeler called “Showboat.” The choice of this
theme and the emphasis on motion, beauty, fluffiness and
perception of theme resulted in a first place float for Chi
Omega and Phi Kappa Theta this year.

